
[1]faithlessness

   FA'ITHLESSNESS, n.

   1. Unbelief, as to revealed religion.

   2. Perfidy; treachery; disloyalty; as in subjects.

   3. Violation of promises or covenants; inconstancy; as of husband or
   wife.
